Average monthly rodent investigations launched in response to 311 complaints have increased sevenfold in Community District 9 since January 2020.

In 2020, 95 rodent investigations, on average, were conducted each month. So far in 2023, an average of 661 investigations have been launched each month.

In July 2022, 1657 rodent investigations were launched in Community District 9.
